\begin_layout Abstract
This chapter presents an incomplete review of the Gauss-Kuzmin-Wirsing (GKW)
 operator.
 The GKW operator is the transfer operator of the Gauss map, and thus has
 connections to the theory of continued fractions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
The operator has a complicated structure, and has not been fully solved
 yet.
 Eigenvalues and eigenfunctions can be obtained numerically, but little
 else is known in the mathematical literature.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
